4:
Mngh! What a beautiful day... Sun's
out, breeze feels nice...
10:
H-hold your fire, Ruelle! Why are you
doing this?!
14:
Because my Prince Charming still
isn't here yet!
18:
What does that have to do with this
violence?!
27:
Whoa, whoa! What's the big idea,
Ruelle?!
31:
Alk, get out of the way... Light's about
to get his champion powers back!
37:
Champions are heroes, right? And
heroes awaken to their true
potential when their lives are in
danger!
41:
Listen, I know the truth hurts, but
Light's powers are really gone...
45:
I already used up everything I had
left. Regaining my powers is an
impossibility.
50:
Why'd you go and use them when I
wasn't around?!
55:
I'm sorry... Wait, why should I be
sorry? I didn't do anything wrong!
60:
*wail* Then who's going to be the
Prince Charming that'll free me?!
65:
I've been wondering about this for a
while now, but how exactly is your
Prince Charming meant to break
your curse?
69:
As if I'd know. This whole thing was
my father's fault.
72:
He had a whole library of magic
tomes. It would've been a pain to go
through them all, even if I could read
them in the first place.
75:
Uh... Maybe you should've at least
looked into it a little?
80:
Take us there, Ruelle. I should be
able to decipher at least some of
those tomes.
83:
I may not be a champion anymore,
but I still have ways I can help out.
86:
...This is exactly how you end up in
these situations, Light...
91:
Eh... Well... I guess it couldn't hurt to
show you.
98:
...Another magic tome. Exactly how
many are there?
101:
A lot more than I predicted, that's for
sure...
108:
Hehe, now do you understand where
I was coming from?
111:
Anybody would give up after seeing
this
115: All right, let's get to it.
134: Kill me. I'm so tired. This is the worst...
155:
Doing the world a favor. It was just a
bunch of gross garbage.
157:
He kept calling me a test subject for
his spell of eternal life or whatever...
160:
Then rambled on and on about
himself for ages. I'd rather not read
his egocentric poetry, thanks.
163:
Are you... sure about this? That all
sounds kinda important.
167:
Eh, I found out this curse is pretty
serious business. That's enough
information for me.
171:
Truly? The key to your freedom
could be in that smoking pile.
175:
Yep! Besides, getting my solution
from a book is pretty boring. I'd
rather have something more
romantic play out!
178: Like a kiss from my Prince Charming!
181: Give me the romance of my dreams!
189:
Oh, please. Life's boring without
aspirations, right?
192:
There's so many worlds out there. I
bet at least one has the Prince
Charming that I'm looking for.
195:
I'll gamble on a perfect happy
ending, risks be damned.
199:
...If that's the path you've chosen,
then we'll walk it with you.
204: Huh? Why? I don't need your help.
213:
Because I'm not going to be
searching for my Prince
Charmingthey'll be finding me!
216:
I know my dreams will come true if I
hold onto them!
220:
That's... a positive outlook, to be
sure...
223:
Normally, you don't wait for
someone else to make your dreams
come true...
230:
Come find me as soon as you can,
my Prince Charming.
